	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I subscribe to a Monk email list and visit a couple of monk message board regularly.  You can learn a lot from keeping active in these things.  Here are a few tips I've learned.<BR>
<BR>
1.  Agility is really all that matters when deciding where to put your points initially.  I did not know this when I made my monk, splitting my points between STR and AGI.  STR doesn't matter bc you really never want to carry over 15 weight bc of the Armor Class penalty.<BR>
<BR>
2.  Dual Wield.  This is a very good skill for the monk, one I did not know about until level six.  Until that time I had carried a lantern in my hand.  Instead, carry a firebeetle eye (or better yet a Lesser or Greater lightstone) in your inventory.  This frees up both hands and helps dual wield go up faster.<BR>
<BR>
3.  Levels 1 - 15.  I personally headed over to Misty Thicket (attached to Rivervale) around level 5.  I stayed there until level 9 (although its a viable place to level up to 14).  It's not ever very crowded and you can level pretty quickly if you play a lot and get with good groups.<BR>
<BR>
4.  Armor - this is the greatest debate.  I'd recommend a full set of cloth, then maybe supplement a few pieces of leather (face, neck, gloves, shoulders).  Later you'll want netted, woven, snakeskin, lupine, and mesh.  These are all the equivalents of normal armors only lighter.<BR>
I won't go into all that here.<BR>
<BR>
5.  Freeport Monks guild has &quot;sash&quot; quests, while Qeynos Monks guild has &quot;headband&quot; quests.  You'll want to complete both sets of quests eventually.<BR>
<BR>
6.  Skills.  I've decided to put all my pracs into Mend, up to level 8.  Then I'm going to use the rest for Feign Death.  I may also use a few to jump start Double Attack.<BR>
<BR>
The monk is a great class, and it's been argued that the monk at the highest levels is the best fighter bar none.<BR>
<BR>
Senjen<BR>
9th level Monk<BR>
Tunare<BR>
<BR>

