			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The only fact that I found not mentioned in my esteemed colleages accounts is that as a human the monk has the advantage that his/her core skills are not limited (or at least limited less than) other races.  Specifically, if you've ever noticed that your skills won't go beyond a certain point until you level?  Well with a human that point either doesn't exist or is much higher.  In general I have found that the skill level is about five times one plus your level (a fifth level character will max out at 30).  But my monk at 7th level with three bars had dual wield up to 58, with a non human that level would have maxed out at 40.  BIG advantage.  Oh...and believe me us on the Sunscreen.  :-)
				</font>
